<s> I think it's taking the text to text view of canonicalization.  </s>
<s> In the first part it is just repeating the requirement in the XML 1.0 Recommendation that all XML parser must understand UTF-8 and UTF-16 encodings.  </s>
<s> In the second phrase, it is syaing that if your parser understands some non-UCS encoding, it must translate that to UCS code pooints.  </s>
<s> Don't know about a parser but a schema verifier would, I think.  </s>
<s> If it knows that some attribute value is a URI, who knows what it might do to it... knowledge can be a dangerous thing.  </s>
<s> Donald  </s>
